# Pluralized Array

This script reads an array from the supplied parameters, favouring the singular parameter and returns an actual array.

The script receives these parameters:

- `singular`: An optional value
- `plural`: An optional list of values, or a string containing space-separated values.

* If singular parameter is provided, then the result will be an array with one element
* Otherwise:
  * If the plural parameter is an actual array, then the result will be that array
  * Otherwise: the result will be the value of the plural parameter splitted by spaces

The resulting array is returned in a variable `pluralized_array`.

## Input parameters

- singular: {{ include.singular }}
- plural: {{ include.plural }}

{% if include.singular %}

## Singular parameter provided

	{% assign pluralized_array = site.data.arrays.empty %}
	{% assign pluralized_array = pluralized_array | push: include.singular %}

{% elsif include.plural %}

## Plural parameter provided

	{% assign pluralized_array = include.plural | push: 'dummy' %}
	{% assign tmp1 = include.plural | size %}
	{% assign tmp2 = pluralized_array | size %}

	{% if tmp2 > tmp1 %}
		{% assign pluralized_array = include.plural %}
	{% else %}
		{% assign pluralized_array = include.plural | split: ' ' %}
	{% endif %}

	{% assign tmp1 = null %}
	{% assign tmp2 = null %}

{% else %}

	{% assign pluralized_array = null %}

{% endif %}

